quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,95,"Indeed, Allah is the Splitter of the grain and the fruit stone. He brings out the living from the dead{1}, and<i class="s">(He is) </i>the Bringer Out of the dead from the living{2}. Such is Allah, so how can you<a class="sup"><sup>pl </sup></a>be averted<i class="s">(from the truth) </i>?",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift in Arabic from a nominal sentence to a verbal sentence.,footnotes:2:A grammatical shift in Arabic from a verbal sentence to a nominal sentence.
  6,96,"<i class=""s"">(He is) </i>the Splitter of the daybreak, and <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Asem, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…and the Maker of the night (as a time) for rest…”</span>
  6,97,"And it is He Who made for you the stars, that you may be guided by them in the darkness<i class=""s"">(es) </i>of land and sea. Surely, We{1}have detailed the signs for people who know.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 3rd person to 1st person.
  6,98,"And it is He Who initiated you from a single self, then <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr and Rouh read it as: “…then a settled one and a stored one.”</span>,footnotes:2:A grammatical shift from 3<sup>rd</sup> person to 1 person to 1<sup>st</sup> person. person.
  6,99,"And it is He who sent down water from the sky, and with it We<a class=",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 3<sup>rd</sup> person to 1 person to 1<sup>st</sup> person. person.,footnotes:2:A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense.,footnotes:3:In kind.,footnotes:4:In taste.
  6,100,"Yet they made for Allah associates—the unseen beings{1}—although He created them, and <span class=",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is <i>jinn</i> which are unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.,footnotes:2:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Nafie’ and Abu Ja’far read it as: “...and they kept inventing for Him sons and daughters,”</span>
  6,101,"Originator of the heavens and the earth—how can He have offspring when He never had a consort? And He created everything, and He is All-Knowing of everything."
